From: Design System
Subject: [PATCH] design-tokens: split --color-accent into brand + --color-action

Introduces `--color-action` as a sibling to `--color-accent` so the
interactive accent can shift register per theme without dragging the
brand color with it.

- Dark theme: --color-action == --color-accent (both forest green).
  Visually identical to current behavior.
- Light theme: --color-action becomes indigo (#4f46e5). Buttons, links,
  focused inputs, focus rings, segmented-toggle active states, and the
  SELECTED node ring shift to indigo on cream. Logo, leaf icon, tree
  edges, and ambient gradients stay green via --color-accent.

Rationale: green-on-cream reads generic-wellness; indigo-on-cream reads
editorial / "reflection, not therapy" — fits the brand voice better.
The forest stays the forest; only the *actions* shift register. Dark
theme is unchanged because the dark forest already carries the
editorial weight on its own.

---
 frontend/src/styles/theme.css | 41 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 38 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/frontend/src/styles/theme.css b/frontend/src/styles/theme.css
--- a/frontend/src/styles/theme.css
+++ b/frontend/src/styles/theme.css
@@ -25,12 +25,29 @@
   --color-text-muted: #7a9a84;
   --color-text-inverse: #0a1a0f;
 
-  /* Accent */
+  /* Accent — brand / content color.
+     Used for the logomark, leaf icon, tree-edge "default", ambient hover
+     tints, soft surface gradients. Stays GREEN in both themes so brand
+     identity is consistent. */
   --color-accent: #2d8a5e;
   --color-accent-hover: #24704c;
   --color-accent-subtle: rgba(45, 138, 94, 0.12);
   --color-accent-focus-ring: rgba(45, 138, 94, 0.35);
 
+  /* Action — interactive accent.
+     Used for primary buttons, links, focused input borders, focus rings,
+     checkbox checked state, segmented-toggle active state, the SELECTED
+     ring on a node. GREEN in dark, INDIGO in light — see [data-theme="light"]
+     override below. Rule of thumb: anything the user *does* uses --color-action;
+     anything that *represents the brand or a tree* uses --color-accent. */
+  --color-action: #2d8a5e;
+  --color-action-hover: #24704c;
+  --color-action-subtle: rgba(45, 138, 94, 0.12);
+  --color-action-focus-ring: rgba(45, 138, 94, 0.35);
+  --color-action-border: rgba(45, 138, 94, 0.3);
+
   /* Danger */
   --color-danger: #ef4444;
   --color-danger-bg: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
@@ -224,6 +241,17 @@
   --color-accent-subtle: rgba(52, 160, 102, 0.08);
   --color-accent-focus-ring: rgba(52, 160, 102, 0.25);
 
+  /* Action turns INDIGO in light — editorial / "reflection, not therapy".
+     Green-on-cream reads generic-wellness; indigo-on-cream reads literary
+     and considered, which fits the brand voice better. The forest stays the
+     forest (logo, leaf, tree edges keep --color-accent green); only the
+     *actions* shift register. */
+  --color-action: #4f46e5;
+  --color-action-hover: #4338ca;
+  --color-action-subtle: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.07);
+  --color-action-focus-ring: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.25);
+  --color-action-border: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.3);
+
   --color-danger: #dc2626;
   --color-danger-bg: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.06);
   --color-danger-border: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.2);
@@ -276,7 +304,7 @@
 
   --color-node-bg: #ffffff;
   --color-node-border: #d4cec6;
-  --color-node-selected: #34a066;
+  --color-node-selected: #4f46e5;
   --color-node-handle: #9aa5b2;
 
   --color-lifebar-fill: rgba(52, 160, 102, 0.12);
@@ -340,12 +368,12 @@ h4 {
 }
 
 a {
-  color: var(--color-accent);
+  color: var(--color-action);
   text-decoration: none;
   transition: var(--transition-colors);
 }
 
 a:hover {
-  color: var(--color-accent-hover);
+  color: var(--color-action-hover);
 }
 
 /* --- Form defaults --- */
@@ -369,8 +397,8 @@ textarea {
 select:focus,
 textarea:focus {
   outline: none;
-  border-color: var(--color-border-focus);
-  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-accent-focus-ring);
+  border-color: var(--color-action);
+  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-action-focus-ring);
 }
 
 label {
@@ -430,14 +458,14 @@ button {
 }
 
 .btn--primary {
-  background: var(--color-accent);
+  background: var(--color-action);
   color: var(--color-text-inverse);
-  border-color: var(--color-accent);
+  border-color: var(--color-action);
 }
 
 .btn--primary:hover {
-  background: var(--color-accent-hover);
+  background: var(--color-action-hover);
 }
 
 .btn--danger {
-- 
